.Dd April 11, 2026
.Dt MANEATER.TOML 5
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm maneater.toml
.Nd configuration file for maneater
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
is the configuration file for
.Xr maneater 1 .
It uses TOML format and controls model selection, embedding prefixes,
and manpath discovery.
.Sh FILE HIERARCHY
Configuration files are loaded and merged in order:
.Bl -enum
.It
.Pa ~/.config/maneater/maneater.toml
(global).
Falls back to
.Pa ~/.config/maneater/models.toml
if the primary file does not exist.
.It
Each parent directory between
.Ev HOME
and the current working directory.
.It
.Pa ./maneater.toml
(project-local).
.El
.Pp
Later files override earlier ones.
Models are merged by name; keys from the overlay replace keys in the base,
while unset keys are preserved.
Manpath include lists accumulate: they are appended across hierarchy levels.
The
.Va manpath.no-auto
field is replaced entirely if present in an overlay.
.Sh TOP-LEVEL KEYS
.Bl -tag -width "default"
.It Va default
Name of the default model.
Must match a key in the
.Va models
table.
Required when multiple models are configured; optional when only one
model exists (that model is used automatically).
.El
.Sh MODELS
Each model is a sub-table under
.Va models
keyed by an arbitrary name.
.Bl -tag -width "document-prefix"
.It Va path
Absolute path to a GGUF model file.
Supports
.Ev $VAR
and
.Ev ${VAR}
environment variable expansion.
Required.
.It Va query-prefix
String prepended to queries before embedding.
Used for asymmetric search models.
Optional.
.It Va document-prefix
String prepended to documents before embedding.
Optional.
.El
.Pp
Example:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
default = "nomic"

[models.nomic]
path = "${MANEATER_MODEL_PATH}"
query-prefix = "search_query: "
document-prefix = "search_document: "
.Ed
.Sh MANPATH
The
.Va manpath
table controls how
.Nm maneater
discovers man pages beyond the system
.Xr manpath 1 .
.Pp
By default,
.Nm maneater
probes the current working directory for common in-repo man page locations:
.Pp
.Bl -bullet -compact
.It
.Pa man/
.It
.Pa doc/man/
.It
.Pa share/man/
.El
.Pp
Directories that exist are prepended to the system manpath, so project pages
shadow system pages with the same name.
.Bl -tag -width "include"
.It Va include
Array of additional directories to prepend to the manpath.
Relative paths are resolved from the current working directory.
Supports
.Ev $VAR
and
.Ev ${VAR}
environment variable expansion.
Include lists accumulate across hierarchy levels.
.It Va no-auto
When set to
.Cm true ,
disables heuristic probing of
.Pa man/ ,
.Pa doc/man/ ,
and
.Pa share/man/ .
Only explicit
.Va include
paths and the system manpath are used.
Default:
.Cm false .
.El
.Pp
Example:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
[manpath]
include = ["vendor/man", "${PROJECT_ROOT}/result/share/man"]
.Ed
.Pp
To disable heuristic probing in a project:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
[manpath]
no-auto = true
.Ed
.Sh EXAMPLES
Minimal configuration with a single model:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
[models.nomic]
path = "/opt/models/nomic-embed-text-v1.5.Q8_0.gguf"
.Ed
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr maneater 1 ,
.Xr moxy 1 ,
.Xr toml 5
